Our cat mew died recently.  <br />
<br />
We took her to a local vet where the vets in charge of the practise graciously allowed us to make payment arrangements in order for our cat to be seen.   Nobody  could figure out what was wrong so they gave her some fluids and antibiotics and sent us home with instructions to bring her back if she got worse.  When she took a turn for the worse the asshats at the front desk basically told us that since we already owed them money we could pay up front and extra for not having a prior appointment we could take our sick cat home to go die. Once we got to speak with the doctor he could clearly see that she wasn't well and agreed to see her anyway.<br />
<br />
It turns out the prognosis was grim, total kidney failure, cause unknown.  She was suffering and had to be put down.  I've never had to do this and it was fucking heartbreaking to hold her while the vet injected her but there was nothing else to be done for it and so we said goodbye to the smallest member of our family.<br />
<br />
So we go today to make a payment on our bill and pick up poor mews ashes and that heartless bitch of an office manager tells us<br />
 A) They wont sell us flea meds for our other 2 cats unless we pay our bill in full first, this is not the original agreement<br />
 B) They will not give us her ashes until they are paid<br />
<br />
Thank you for making our fallen family member a bargaining chip to ensure you get your $145.  I hope it was worth your heart and soul you fucking evil heartless bitch.</div>


